                "title": "Sircah: A tool for the detection and visualization of alternative transcripts", 
                "abstract": "Sircah is a flexible tool for the detection, analysis and visualization of alternative transcripts. It takes as input gene models or spliced alignments and creates a database of alternative transcription events: alternative transcription initiation and polyadenylation, alternative 3′ and 5′ splice-site usage, skipped exons and retained introns. The results can be visualized in a variety of ways, allowing the creation of publication quality images. © The Author 2008. Published by Oxford University Press. All rights reserved.", 
